						<summary>

						<p>This is much damaged. It seems to record a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva of Avanigandarva-Īśvara-gṛiham in Kuṉṟak-kūṟṟam by one Atiśūraṉ••••••• of Maḻapāḍi in [Vā]ṇagappāḍi, who had deposited the amount with two <hi rend="italic">nagarattār.</hi> The inscription also refers to a later order (the nature of which is not known) of <hi rend="bold">Aḍigaḷ Paḻavēṭṭaraiyar Kaṇḍan [Amuda]nār</hi>, made in the 16th year of <hi rend="bold">Uttamasōḻadēvar</hi> Parakēsarivarman, evidently about the utilisation of this amount.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
